text: Hyphaene coriacea, the Lala palm, is a species of palm tree native to the eastern Afrotropics. It occurs in eastern Africa from Somalia to Kwazulu- Natal, South Africa, and is also found in the coastal flats of Madagascar and on Juan de Nova Island in the Mozambique Channel Islands. ==See also== * Fan palm ==References== coriacea Category:Flora of Ethiopia Category:Flora of Somalia Category:Flora of Kenya Category:Flora of Tanzania Category:Flora of Mozambique Category:Flora of KwaZulu-Natal Category:Flora of the Northern Provinces Category:Flora of the Mozambique Channel Islands Category:Flora of Madagascar Category:Trees of Africa Category:Plants described in 1788
